1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:11,667
<i> The client is king.</i>

2
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,267
<i>That's why she had no right
to disrespect</i>

3
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:14,533
<i> and hurt Mr. Valderama.</i>

4
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:17,267
<i>I still run and own this company</i>

5
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,333
<i> so my word stands.</i>

6
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:19,300
<i> You don't work here anymore.</i>

7
00:00:19,433 --> 00:00:21,000
<i> You don't have to fire me.</i>

8
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:22,467
<i> Because I quit.</i>

9
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:24,200
<i>I wish there's,
there's something I can do</i>

10
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:25,200
<i> to fix this.</i>

11
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:27,700
<i>Forget it, he's a very
powerful man.</i>

12
00:00:27,833 --> 00:00:29,067
<i>There's bleeding inside
the skull.</i>

13
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,967
<i>We need emergency surgery
to avoid serious brain damage.</i>

14
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,200
<i> Jobert, wake up!</i>

15
00:00:34,367 --> 00:00:37,300
<i>How are we supposed to come up
with 300,000 pesos?</i>

16
00:00:37,433 --> 00:00:38,600
<i> Why don't you call Sir Edward?</i>

17
00:00:38,733 --> 00:00:40,233
<i>The Torrecampos
are insanely rich.</i>

18
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:41,867
<i>300,000 pesos
is nothing to them.</i>

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,200
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

20
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,800
<i> Didn't I already fire you?</i>

21
00:00:47,667 --> 00:00:50,467
Why are you stalking us
at our own house?

22
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,233
Sir, Sir Greg,

23
00:00:53,367 --> 00:00:54,633
Sir Paolo...

24
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:58,400
My brother
is in critical condition.

25
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:02,667
He needs surgery right away.

26
00:01:02,800 --> 00:01:04,767
I'm begging you both.

27
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:06,200
Please help me.

28
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:10,600
I have no one else to turn to.

29
00:01:15,900 --> 00:01:16,700
Dad.

30
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:19,233
Why don't we just help her?

31
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:20,900
What?

32
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:21,867
It's not a big deal.

33
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:24,200
And she's a great agent.

34
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,833
Better to keep her than
let another company steal her,

35
00:01:26,967 --> 00:01:27,967
right?

36
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:30,933
We don't need an insubordinate
like her!

37
00:01:31,067 --> 00:01:33,600
She'll just talk back
to me again.

38
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:35,967
We can find someone better.

39
00:01:36,967 --> 00:01:39,700
Sir, you're my last hope.

40
00:01:41,333 --> 00:01:43,667
Please, I'm begging you.

41
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:47,933
My brother's life
is on the line.

42
00:01:48,067 --> 00:01:50,467
He needs surgery now.

43
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:53,300
I can't lose him.

44
00:02:43,633 --> 00:02:46,133
Stop wasting my time,
Miss Castillo.

45
00:02:46,267 --> 00:02:50,233
No matter how much you beg,
my answer is still no.

46
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:52,300
Sir Greg, please...

47
00:02:53,467 --> 00:02:56,667
My brother's life
depends on this.

48
00:03:04,133 --> 00:03:05,233
That's enough.

49
00:03:05,367 --> 00:03:07,467
Someone might see you here.

50
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:10,600
They'll think you're just
another woman chasing after me.

51
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:11,700
Don't worry about it.

52
00:03:11,833 --> 00:03:13,500
I'll see what I can do, okay?

53
00:03:13,633 --> 00:03:15,367
- Dad.
- No!

54
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:17,633
It's not going to happen, Paolo!

55
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:20,333
If you want to be president
of the company someday,

56
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,667
you can't let emotions lead you.

57
00:03:23,933 --> 00:03:25,800
People will just take
advantage of you.

58
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,233
Leave now, Miss Castillo.

59
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:36,067
Let this be your last warning.

60
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:39,567
Come back here again,
and I'll call the police.

61
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:46,967
Go!

62
00:04:15,967 --> 00:04:17,067
Ma?

63
00:04:17,200 --> 00:04:19,967
Marj, how did it go, sweetheart?

64
00:04:22,433 --> 00:04:24,167
I'm sorry, Mom.

65
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,633
I did everything I could.

66
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:29,933
I swallowed my pride.

67
00:04:30,067 --> 00:04:34,467
I begged them, but they still
refused to help.

68
00:04:38,667 --> 00:04:43,967
Marj, maybe we should look
for your father.

69
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:47,267
Ask him for help.

70
00:04:47,400 --> 00:04:49,267
Let's ask your dad for help.

71
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,200
Mom...

72
00:04:51,333 --> 00:04:54,033
Dad abandoned us.

73
00:04:54,167 --> 00:04:58,200
He doesn't even care if we've
eaten or where we sleep,

74
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:00,200
whether we're on the streets
or not.

75
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:04,467
Do you really think he'll
suddenly feel sorry for us?

76
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:08,100
Grow a conscience to help us?

77
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:10,967
Don't think about Dad anymore.

78
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:15,733
Marj, we have no other choice.

79
00:05:15,867 --> 00:05:20,233
Your brother needs to be saved
before it's too late!

80
00:05:22,467 --> 00:05:24,300
Marj!

81
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:43,333
Sir, don't we have plans today?

82
00:05:43,467 --> 00:05:44,633
No, Oscar.

83
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:46,333
You can rest.

84
00:05:46,467 --> 00:05:48,533
Wow, Sir, what a miracle.

85
00:05:48,667 --> 00:05:50,000
No ladies lined up tonight?

86
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,533
None, I'm not in the mood.

87
00:05:53,667 --> 00:05:54,633
Oh, I get it.

88
00:05:54,767 --> 00:05:56,533
Is this about the woman
who visited earlier?

89
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:59,033
Your former employee?

90
00:05:59,167 --> 00:06:02,900
I noticed the way
you looked at her.

91
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:05,600
Oscar, you talk too much.

92
00:06:05,733 --> 00:06:06,600
Go on.

93
00:06:06,733 --> 00:06:08,167
Go get some rest.

94
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:09,567
Yes, Sir.

95
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:22,700
<i>PA: Paging Doc Lazaro to ICU.
Paging Doc Lazaro to ICU.</i>

96
00:06:24,700 --> 00:06:26,800
That's Jobert's doctor, Mom.

97
00:06:26,933 --> 00:06:30,067
Marj, what if something
happened to him?

98
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:32,433
Oh, God, please no.

99
00:06:37,167 --> 00:06:39,200
Jobert.

100
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:41,133
Jobert...

101
00:06:41,300 --> 00:06:42,467
Jobert.

102
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:44,100
Jobert.

103
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:52,533
- Doc!
- Doctor, how is my son?

104
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:31,733
Diazepam, 10 mg IV, now!

105
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,467
Kate, monitor his vitals.

106
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:18,067
Push!

107
00:08:29,433 --> 00:08:31,633
He's stabilized for now.

108
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:34,033
Kindly monitor the patient
closely.

109
00:09:01,067 --> 00:09:02,667
Ma.

110
00:09:07,867 --> 00:09:09,767
I'm Dr. Gatchalian.

111
00:09:09,900 --> 00:09:13,667
Dr. Lazaro endorsed
Jobert's case to me.

112
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:17,733
He needs surgery immediately.

113
00:09:17,867 --> 00:09:22,433
If not, it'll put more pressure
on his brain.

114
00:09:22,567 --> 00:09:25,567
He could fall
into a coma or die.

115
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,600
Doctor...

116
00:09:29,733 --> 00:09:31,200
what do we do?

117
00:09:31,333 --> 00:09:33,500
We don't have the money yet.

118
00:09:33,633 --> 00:09:36,467
We're still trying to find it.

119
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,833
I understand.

120
00:09:37,967 --> 00:09:40,667
But you need to act fast.

121
00:09:41,767 --> 00:09:44,433
We already gave him
anti-seizure med

122
00:09:44,567 --> 00:09:48,600
and drugs to reduce
the pressure.

123
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,000
But those are only temporary.

124
00:09:52,433 --> 00:09:54,167
The bleeding is getting worse.

125
00:09:54,300 --> 00:09:55,533
Every second we lose,

126
00:09:56,567 --> 00:09:59,433
we're risking permanent
brain damage.

127
00:09:59,567 --> 00:10:06,433
Doctor, please, can you operate
on my brother now?

128
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,567
We'll pay.

129
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:09,133
We'll find the money.

130
00:10:09,267 --> 00:10:11,867
We'll borrow,
I'll do anything, Doctor.

131
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,567
Just save my brother.

132
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:15,667
Please.

133
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:18,433
I want to help, Miss Castillo...

134
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:24,067
But the hospital can't proceed
without at least a deposit.

135
00:10:26,367 --> 00:10:29,033
Doctor, go ahead
with the surgery.

136
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:33,933
I'll take care of everything.

137
00:10:59,733 --> 00:11:01,567
Marj, coffee for everyone.

138
00:11:05,033 --> 00:11:07,467
- Thank you.
- Welcome po.

139
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:12,067
Thank you so much, Sir Paolo.

140
00:11:13,133 --> 00:11:16,167
Does your dad know
you're helping me?

141
00:11:17,233 --> 00:11:20,533
If I told him,
he'd probably stop me.

142
00:11:21,633 --> 00:11:24,867
I decided to help
just to make it up to you.

143
00:11:25,900 --> 00:11:27,733
Marj...

144
00:11:27,867 --> 00:11:29,700
I saw the CCTV footage.

145
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:44,067
<i>Miss Tough Girl really is scary
when she's mad.</i>

146
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:52,000
<i>I've confirmed
you were telling the truth.</i>

147
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:58,333
I'm sorry it took me so long
to believe you.

148
00:12:06,933 --> 00:12:08,100
Doctor...

149
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,600
How's my son?

150
00:12:09,733 --> 00:12:12,500
The operation was successful.

151
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:15,333
We were able to relieve
the pressure in his brain.

152
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:19,467
His vital signs are stable now.

153
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:22,167
Mom, did you hear that?

154
00:12:22,300 --> 00:12:24,233
Jobert's safe.

155
00:12:24,367 --> 00:12:25,567
Thank God, Marj.

156
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,967
Thank you, Doctor.

157
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:27,767
You're welcome.

158
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,300
Excuse me.

159
00:12:29,433 --> 00:12:30,467
Thank you, Doctor.

160
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:33,733
Sir Paolo...

161
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:37,100
thank you so much.

162
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:42,033
I'll never forget
what you did for us.

163
00:12:42,167 --> 00:12:46,100
I promise I'll pay you back.

164
00:12:46,233 --> 00:12:49,733
If it weren't for you,
we might've lost Jobert.

165
00:12:49,900 --> 00:12:51,767
No, Marj...

166
00:12:51,900 --> 00:12:54,233
You're making me
sound like a hero.

167
00:12:54,367 --> 00:12:56,433
All I did was provide the money.

168
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:59,400
The real hero is you, Marj.

169
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:03,967
No matter how big the problem
was, you never gave up.

170
00:13:04,100 --> 00:13:06,000
That's why
you're Miss Tough Girl.

171
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,667
Sorry, sorry, Sir.

172
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:33,133
I just got carried away.

173
00:13:33,267 --> 00:13:34,467
It's okay.

174
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,500
I always have that effect
on a woman.

175
00:13:38,233 --> 00:13:39,667
Ah, I should get going.

176
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,400
Dad's been calling me nonstop.

177
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:43,767
Sorry again, Sir.

178
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:47,667
I hope I didn't cause trouble
for you by helping me.

179
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:48,933
No, relax.

180
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:50,667
I'll handle my dad.

181
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,967
Take some time off.

182
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,767
Wait until your brother
gets stronger.

183
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:55,433
Once he's fully recovered,

184
00:13:55,600 --> 00:13:57,733
then you can go back
to work, okay?

185
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,767
Thank you so much.

186
00:14:02,133 --> 00:14:02,867
You're welcome.

187
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,033
I'll go ahead now.

188
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:05,533
- Thank you.
- All right.

189
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:19,833
Sir Paolo's not so bad.

190
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:21,233
He seems to be just
a terror boss.

191
00:14:21,367 --> 00:14:23,800
Turns out he's actually kind.

192
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:31,800
Ah, Weng.

193
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:34,367
Paolo!

194
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:40,033
Yes. Dad?

195
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:42,467
Why haven't you been
answering my calls?

196
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,033
You missed our family dinner.

197
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,767
Let me guess,
you chose chasing women again?

198
00:14:48,867 --> 00:14:50,733
Dad, today's my day off
from being a stud.

199
00:14:50,867 --> 00:14:52,467
It's hard juggling
three women, you know.

200
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:57,133
I'm not joking, Paolo.

201
00:14:57,267 --> 00:14:59,200
Where did you really come from?

202
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:01,833
Dad, I went to the hospital.

203
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:05,867
I helped Marj so her brother
could have surgery.

204
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:09,233
And I also asked her
to come back to the company.

205
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:12,467
Are you out of your mind?

206
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,233
I already rejected that woman!

207
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:17,367
Why did you go against
my decision?

208
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:20,133
Dad, please don't stress
yourself out.

209
00:15:20,267 --> 00:15:21,367
You always taught me

210
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:23,667
that the company
should always come first.

211
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:26,433
I'm just following your example.

212
00:15:27,700 --> 00:15:30,567
And how exactly did helping that
woman benefit the company?

213
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:34,733
Dad, I know women.

214
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:39,200
And Marj is the type who fights
back and never quits.

215
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:41,533
What if she files a case
against our company

216
00:15:41,667 --> 00:15:45,100
for harassment and wrongful
termination?

217
00:15:46,500 --> 00:15:49,067
You know, hon,
Paolo has a point.

218
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:52,667
Maybe it's better
if we help her,

219
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,367
so the situation doesn't
get out of hand.

220
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:57,733
The last thing we need
is a scandal.

221
00:15:57,867 --> 00:15:58,733
No!

222
00:15:58,867 --> 00:16:00,233
Don't act like you know
better than me!

223
00:16:01,267 --> 00:16:04,067
This is my turf
that I am protecting!

224
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,500
If we go against Mr. Valderama,

225
00:16:06,633 --> 00:16:08,600
our business will suffer!

226
00:16:09,533 --> 00:16:10,467
I know.

227
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,933
But if this spreads,

228
00:16:13,067 --> 00:16:15,300
it won't just affect
our business.

229
00:16:15,433 --> 00:16:17,200
It will destroy us.

230
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,200
It will destroy our business.

231
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,967
Dad, one social media post
is all it takes,

232
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:27,367
and the whole world
turns against us.

233
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:31,867
They'll say the Torrecampos
fired an employee

234
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:35,333
to protect a sexual predator
and abuser.

235
00:16:35,467 --> 00:16:36,333
Dad, is that what you want?

236
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:40,733
I'll let this slide for now.

237
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,300
But if you go
behind my back again,

238
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:46,067
you'll deal with me.

239
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:46,900
Do you understand?

240
00:16:47,667 --> 00:16:48,667
Yes, Dad.

241
00:17:04,300 --> 00:17:05,800
Sir Paolo really is impressive.

242
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:09,300
I never thought
he'd help that Marj.

243
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,333
You should've stopped him.

244
00:17:12,467 --> 00:17:13,900
What? Why would I?

245
00:17:15,333 --> 00:17:18,300
Look, Sir Greg ended up
scolding Sir Paolo.

246
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:23,133
You know how Sir Greg hates it
when anyone challenges him

247
00:17:23,267 --> 00:17:24,300
or goes against him.

248
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:28,100
Exactly.

249
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:30,567
You know, I've noticed
that everyone in this house

250
00:17:30,700 --> 00:17:33,333
seems terrified of Sir Greg.

251
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:37,633
Even Ma'am Regina
always gives in to him.

252
00:17:38,933 --> 00:17:39,567
Have you noticed?

253
00:17:43,967 --> 00:17:46,133
There's a lot you don't know yet
about this family.

254
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,367
The Torrecampos
have many secrets.

255
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:56,767
They hide everything
to protect their image.

256
00:17:58,167 --> 00:18:02,933
Because for Sir Greg,
what matters most

257
00:18:03,067 --> 00:18:07,533
is looking like
the perfect family.

258
00:18:27,033 --> 00:18:28,033
Come on, go inside.

259
00:18:28,167 --> 00:18:29,533
There.

260
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:31,733
I'm sure you missed this house.

261
00:18:33,267 --> 00:18:34,933
I miss home.

262
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:38,667
Hi, Pong!

263
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:42,600
Water, water, water.

264
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,900
Here, drink some water first.

265
00:18:52,033 --> 00:18:53,200
Just a little.

266
00:18:53,333 --> 00:18:55,033
That's it.

267
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:55,833
Very good.

268
00:18:56,867 --> 00:18:58,833
Careful. It bites.

269
00:18:58,967 --> 00:19:00,833
- I missed you.
- Thank God.

270
00:19:01,867 --> 00:19:04,033
Your brother's recovering fast.

271
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:06,600
Look at him, so energetic.

272
00:19:06,733 --> 00:19:07,767
He's so happy.

273
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:11,300
Mom, can you watch Jobert?

274
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:13,500
I need to go back to work.

275
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,767
Are you sure you want
to go back there?

276
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:21,367
What if Sir Greg
targets you again?

277
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:22,900
Mom, I don't have a choice.

278
00:19:23,867 --> 00:19:25,867
I need to pay Sir Paolo back.

279
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:36,900
Bert, Bert.

280
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,367
Girl, they say you're super
famous here now.

281
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:46,033
The whole floor's talking
about your grand comeback.

282
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,133
I can't understand
anything you're saying.

283
00:19:50,233 --> 00:19:53,667
They're saying
you're famous now.

284
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:54,967
You had your grand comeback

285
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:57,033
because you're close
to Sir Paolo.

286
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,367
How are they supposed
to get any work done

287
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,467
when all they do is gossip?

288
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:05,433
Anyway, let's have lunch
together. Okay?

289
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:07,767
Okay.

290
00:20:17,033 --> 00:20:18,367
Why are you still here?

291
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,867
I thought we'd have
lunch together?

292
00:20:21,367 --> 00:20:23,100
I could've asked you
the same thing.

293
00:20:27,033 --> 00:20:28,067
Sir.

294
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:32,767
I see you've settled back in.

295
00:20:34,633 --> 00:20:37,100
Just make sure you don't
cause trouble again.

296
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,733
I'm not as forgiving as Paolo.

297
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:42,767
This is your last chance.

298
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:44,967
Do we understand each other?

299
00:20:46,367 --> 00:20:47,467
Yes, Sir.

300
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:51,400
I'll be keeping an eye on you.

301
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:55,600
One mistake,
and you're out of here.

302
00:20:56,767 --> 00:20:57,633
For good.

303
00:21:15,367 --> 00:21:16,533
- Mom!
- Yes?

304
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:20,467
- What does my baby want?
- Mom?

305
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:22,067
Mom's right here.

306
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:24,133
Are you hungry?

307
00:21:24,267 --> 00:21:25,067
What do you want to eat?

308
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,433
Do you want a snack?

309
00:21:26,567 --> 00:21:28,267
What do you feel
like eating?

310
00:21:30,867 --> 00:21:32,600
You don't want a snack?

311
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:33,767
Then why are you
being so clingy?

312
00:21:33,900 --> 00:21:35,033
What do you really want?

313
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:40,000
I want to see my sister, Mom.

314
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:42,300
I want to see Marj.

315
00:21:42,467 --> 00:21:44,133
Your sister is at work.

316
00:21:44,667 --> 00:21:45,733
But don't worry.

317
00:21:45,867 --> 00:21:47,767
She'll be back later, okay?

318
00:21:49,833 --> 00:21:51,167
I miss my sister, Mom.

319
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:53,333
I miss Marj.

320
00:21:54,067 --> 00:21:56,333
I want to go to her.

321
00:21:56,467 --> 00:21:59,267
Your sister's working.

322
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:00,367
She's busy.

323
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:03,367
We shouldn't bother her.

324
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,067
And you need to rest
here at home, okay?

325
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,633
You're still getting
your strength back.

326
00:22:07,767 --> 00:22:09,367
You just got out
of the hospital.

327
00:22:10,633 --> 00:22:12,200
I'm not sick anymore!

328
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:14,000
I want my sister!

329
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,100
I want Marj!

330
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:16,267
I want Marj!

331
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:21,667
- My sister!
- Okay, okay. Enough.

332
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:24,667
I'll text your sister.

333
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,700
I'll tell her
we're coming to see her.

334
00:22:27,633 --> 00:22:29,067
Stop crying now, okay?

335
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,000
Marj...

336
00:22:30,567 --> 00:22:31,500
Just a moment.

337
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,300
I'm texting your sister.

338
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:41,267
There.

339
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,400
And that's all, Mrs. Tan.

340
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:47,200
Excuse me.

341
00:22:52,833 --> 00:22:53,800
How was it?

342
00:22:55,367 --> 00:22:56,500
The presentation went well.

343
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:01,267
I'll talk to my husband,
but I think it's fine.

344
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:01,833
Thank you.

345
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:03,433
Thank you so much.

346
00:23:03,567 --> 00:23:04,733
You're welcome.

347
00:23:04,867 --> 00:23:05,800
I'll walk you out.

348
00:23:08,500 --> 00:23:09,567
Have a good day.

349
00:23:09,700 --> 00:23:10,500
Thank you.

350
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:24,533
Marj?

351
00:23:26,033 --> 00:23:26,667
Sir Edward!

352
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:29,033
You're back from Iloilo already.

353
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:30,467
How are you?

354
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,100
I mean, how's your brother?

355
00:23:32,233 --> 00:23:33,500
I heard what happened.

356
00:23:34,733 --> 00:23:36,867
I'm sorry I couldn't help.

357
00:23:37,633 --> 00:23:38,500
It's okay.

358
00:23:38,633 --> 00:23:39,333
He's doing better.

359
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:42,200
He's already been discharged.

360
00:23:42,333 --> 00:23:44,467
Good thing Sir Paolo helped me.

361
00:23:45,033 --> 00:23:47,267
He paid
for my brother's surgery.

362
00:23:48,667 --> 00:23:50,467
Yes, I heard about that.

363
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:52,533
And not just that, Sir Edward.

364
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:55,100
He also helped me
get my job back.

365
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,867
Turns out your brother's
actually kind.

366
00:24:01,067 --> 00:24:03,300
I guess I misjudged him.

367
00:24:21,433 --> 00:24:24,200
Jobert, promise me something,
okay?

368
00:24:24,633 --> 00:24:26,133
Behave when we get there.

369
00:24:26,267 --> 00:24:28,100
And we can't stay long.

370
00:24:28,833 --> 00:24:31,333
We don't want to interrupt
your sister's work, all right?

371
00:24:31,467 --> 00:24:32,067
Yes.

372
00:24:32,233 --> 00:24:33,500
I'll behave.

373
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:34,333
Pong, too.

374
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:35,433
That's right.

375
00:24:35,567 --> 00:24:36,700
Very good.

376
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:39,300
- Ma'am! Ma'am!
- Marj!

377
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:40,167
What do you need?

378
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:42,667
This way, please.

379
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,500
Sir, I'm just here
to see my daughter.

380
00:24:45,633 --> 00:24:46,733
She works here.

381
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:48,200
Do you have an ID?

382
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:50,267
Oh, I don't have one, Sir.

383
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:52,433
I don't work here.

384
00:24:52,567 --> 00:24:54,100
My youngest doesn't
have one either.

385
00:24:54,233 --> 00:24:54,967
Do you have an appointment?

386
00:24:56,867 --> 00:24:58,100
Do we need an appointment?

387
00:24:58,233 --> 00:25:00,300
My daughter works here.

388
00:25:00,433 --> 00:25:02,367
Ma'am, you don't have an ID,

389
00:25:02,533 --> 00:25:03,500
and you don't have
an appointment.

390
00:25:03,633 --> 00:25:05,067
You're not allowed to enter.

391
00:25:06,167 --> 00:25:08,367
But my daughter works here.

392
00:25:08,500 --> 00:25:10,133
I can see the turtle.

393
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:12,200
I want the turtle.

394
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:13,133
Do we really need...

395
00:25:13,267 --> 00:25:13,633
I don't have one.

396
00:25:13,767 --> 00:25:15,133
What do I do?

397
00:25:15,267 --> 00:25:16,533
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

398
00:25:16,667 --> 00:25:17,767
You really can't come in.

399
00:25:20,733 --> 00:25:21,400
Turtle...

400
00:25:22,767 --> 00:25:23,533
Please, Sir.

401
00:25:23,667 --> 00:25:24,900
We'll only be a minute.

402
00:25:25,033 --> 00:25:26,067
Hey, hey!

403
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:29,500
- I told you to behave, Jobert.
- Hey! Hey!

404
00:25:29,633 --> 00:25:31,067
Come here!

405
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:35,633
You don't have the right
to hurt my child!

406
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,567
- Let go of me!
- You're hurting my child!

407
00:25:38,700 --> 00:25:40,067
Please have mercy!

408
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:41,033
No!

409
00:25:41,167 --> 00:25:43,500
- No!
- You're hurting my child!

410
00:25:43,633 --> 00:25:47,000
Don't hurt him!
I'm begging you, please!

411
00:25:52,367 --> 00:25:54,267
I just need to stop
by for a second, okay?

412
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,200
No, don't. I'll do it.

413
00:25:55,333 --> 00:25:56,233
I'll take care of it.

414
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:03,833
Let go!

415
00:26:03,967 --> 00:26:05,067
Let go of me!

416
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,233
Hey! What's going on here?

417
00:26:06,367 --> 00:26:07,233
- Let go!
- Let him go!

418
00:26:07,367 --> 00:26:09,200
- Let him go!
- Let go!

419
00:26:09,367 --> 00:26:10,233
Let go!

420
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:11,333
Evelyn.

421
00:26:12,367 --> 00:26:15,433
Jobert didn't do anything wrong,
Sir Paolo.

422
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:17,033
He just wanted to see
his sister.

423
00:26:18,367 --> 00:26:19,400
They got angry.

424
00:26:19,533 --> 00:26:21,300
My son got triggered.

425
00:26:23,233 --> 00:26:26,933
The scene in the lobby
earlier was wild.

426
00:26:27,067 --> 00:26:27,933
Yes, girl.

427
00:26:28,067 --> 00:26:30,000
The guy having a meltdown
looked autistic.

428
00:26:30,133 --> 00:26:30,633
Autistic?

429
00:26:30,767 --> 00:26:32,000
What happened?

430
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:33,900
Good thing the guards
stopped him.

431
00:26:34,033 --> 00:26:35,400
And the woman with him.

432
00:26:36,333 --> 00:26:37,367
The woman with him?

433
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:38,767
She looked like his mom.

434
00:26:39,867 --> 00:26:41,233
Honestly, I feel bad for them.

435
00:26:43,433 --> 00:26:46,367
Kim, how old do you think
the kid you saw downstairs was?

436
00:26:47,367 --> 00:26:49,033
Maybe around 18?

437
00:26:49,167 --> 00:26:49,967
Why?

438
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:51,800
Eighteen?

439
00:26:56,033 --> 00:26:57,733
We need to recoup our losses

440
00:26:57,867 --> 00:27:00,433
by acquiring more
exclusive listings,

441
00:27:00,567 --> 00:27:03,833
specifically Paradiso Escaño
in Batangas.

442
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,900
You wouldn't say no, right?

443
00:27:06,033 --> 00:27:07,600
It's not often I'm impressed.

444
00:27:07,733 --> 00:27:09,933
That's the kind of woman
you should be dating, son.

445
00:27:10,067 --> 00:27:13,300
You don't even have to try
hard for her to like you.

446
00:27:13,433 --> 00:27:14,800
You're a Torrecampo.

447
00:27:14,933 --> 00:27:17,600
I didn't raise you to be weak.

448
00:27:17,767 --> 00:27:19,133
Don't let your brother
outdo you.

449
00:27:20,133 --> 00:27:21,000
I felt so betrayed.

450
00:27:22,167 --> 00:27:23,567
Marj, don't let him fool you.

451
00:27:24,933 --> 00:27:26,200
What are you talking about?

452
00:27:26,333 --> 00:27:28,133
He's not a good guy.

453
00:27:28,267 --> 00:27:29,167
What did you tell her?

454
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:30,533
You made me look like a fool!
